    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a tank of fluid, consisting of two regions separated by a horizontal line. The bottom region is labeled “Fluid.” The right tank wall has the points P and Q indicated from top to bottom, such that point Q is at the horizontal boundary, and point P is a distance 0.5 meter above point Q. Near the middle of the fluid, a laser is submerged 0.5 m below the horizontal boundary and 1.0 meter from the right tank wall. The laser is shown in two different positions, one in which the laser beam points vertically upward and one in which the laser beam is slanted upward and to the right. The angle between the two positions is theta.\" src=\"/images/f740fb07c0fd1796d86e27a5e5826e55.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A laser is submerged in the middle of a tank of fluid, as shown in the figure. The fluid has an index of refraction such that total internal reflection occurs whenever the angle of incidence in the fluid is greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"45 degrees\"><math alttext=\"45 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mn>45</mn><mo>∘</mo></msup></math></span></span> at the surface between the fluid and air. Assume that the surface of the fluid is perfectly smooth and horizontal.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The laser is initially directed vertically upward. Starting at time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t equals 0\"><math alttext=\"t equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>, the laser starts rotating clockwise so that the beam is directed at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> from the vertical, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\"